54.4	Vincenzo_Bellini	Vincenzo Bellini	Vincenzo Salvatore Carmelo Francesco Bellini (3 November 1801 â€“ 23 September 1835) was an Italian opera composer. His greatest works are I Capuleti ed i Montecchi (1830), La sonnambula (1831), Norma (1831), Beatrice di Tenda (1833), and I puritani (1835). Known for his long-flowing melodic lines, for which he was named "the Swan of Catania," Bellini was the quintessential composer of bel canto opera.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Vincenzo_bellini.jpg/220px-Vincenzo_bellini.jpg
